  • Building the LSTM Model
In [178]:
model = Sequential()
model.add(Embedding(vocab_size, 10, input_length = 3))
model.add(LSTM(1000, return_sequences = True))
model.add(LSTM(1000))
model.add(Dense(1000, activation = 'relu'))
model.add(Dense(vocab_size, activation = 'softmax'))

In [238]:
def predict_next_word(model, tokenizer, text):
    sequence = np.array(tokenizer.texts_to_sequences([text]))
    pred = np.argmax(model.predict(sequence))

    for key, value in tokenizer.word_index.items():
        if value == pred:
            print(key)
            return key

Observations¶

  • the model seems to underfit as the performance is poor when predicting using either the training data or the testing data, so the model need to be fine tuned with different hyperparameters such as using:
    • higher epochs and smaller batch sizes.
    • different learning rate.
    • different loss function or optimizer.
  • In terms of data we can apply feature engineering, such as:
    • normalize the data counts to avoid model biasing to any repitative non important words such as (a, the, is, to).
    • lowercasing all the words in order to remove any biasing towards letter case.
    • remove commas, dots and any other non useful signs from the training data.
